template.description: This template can invoke a request to Opensky Network. Alternatively, generate a different flowfile if you have pre-exising data.
template.name: NiFiAirlineTemplate

labels.label:
INVOKE HTTP:
This is the REST API call for Opensky Network's flight data. It provides a file filled with aircraft data over a 1-2 hour time period within the time you make the call. You can only make so many calls before the network locks your requests, however.

SPLITTING JSON:
The Data arrives in a format that looks like this: {"time":1691779818, "states":[["ae1fa5","72150 ","United States",1691779816,1691779818,-115.202,36.2165,null,true,0.19,118.12,null,null,null,"5671",false,0]...]}
The first split separates TIME and STATES.
The second split separates STATES into individual records to be processed.

EXECUTE SQL RECORD:
In this processor, we are inserting data into our database. We only needed to insert 4 items: LATITUDE, LONGITUDE, TIME_POSITION, and ON_GROUND.
GOUDA: If you get the error where you cannot find the Postgresql driver, you will have to replace the driver in the repository with a newly downloaded one (nifi/conf/volumes)

EVALUATE JSON PATH:
Here, for each individual records, we can index the array and assign variable names to them to be accessed by the SQL method
Information on the data itself can be found here: https://openskynetwork.github.io/opensky-api/python.html
